@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Community Guidelines";
}

<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
<p class="text-muted"><em>Last updated: May 2026</em></p>

<p>
    FindActivity is a community for people in the Greater Seattle area to find things to do together.
    These guidelines exist so it stays welcoming, safe, and useful. They apply to every activity you create
    and every interaction you have on the platform.
</p>

<h2>The basics</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Be 18 or over.</strong> FindActivity is adults only.</li>
    <li><strong>Be real.</strong> Use your real name or a recognizable display name. No impersonation.</li>
    <li><strong>Be respectful.</strong> Disagreement is fine. Harassment, slurs, threats, and hate speech are not.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Activities you can post</h2>
<p>Anything legal, free, and friendly. Some examples that work well:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Hikes, bike rides, runs, pickup sports.</li>
    <li>Board game nights, book clubs, language exchanges.</li>
    <li>Coffee meetups, group dinners, museum trips.</li>
    <li>Volunteering, beach cleanups, neighborhood gatherings.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Activities that aren't allowed</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>No sexual or romantic activities.</strong> FindActivity is not a dating app. No "hookup," "play party," or sexually-themed events.</li>
    <li><strong>No paid events or sales.</strong> No ticketed events, no events that require purchases, no MLMs, no recruiting for paid services.</li>
    <li><strong>No illegal activities.</strong> Drug use, underage drinking, theft, vandalism, anything that breaks Washington state or federal law.</li>
    <li><strong>No high-risk activities without proper context.</strong> Things like climbing, scuba, or motorsports are fine if you're clear about skill level and safety, but don't invite strangers into something dangerous without disclosure.</li>
    <li><strong>No hate or extremism.</strong> Events organized around discrimination by race, religion, gender, sexuality, disability, or national origin are removed.</li>
    <li><strong>No content that endangers minors.</strong> Zero tolerance.</li>
    <li><strong>No spam or self-promotion.</strong> Don't use activities to advertise a business, channel, or product.</li>
</ul>

<h2>How you treat people</h2>
<ul>
    <li>RSVP only if you intend to show up. If your plans change, leave the activity so others can join.</li>
    <li>If you're hosting, be a good host: confirm the meeting spot, show up on time, and let people know if it's canceled.</li>
    <li>Reviews should reflect the actual activity. Don't review events you didn't attend, and don't use reviews to vent personal grievances.</li>
    <li>Off-platform contact (texting, social media) should respect the same boundaries you'd use anywhere else. "No" means no.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Safety</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Meet in public, well-trafficked spots, especially the first time.</li>
    <li>Tell a friend or family member where you're going.</li>
    <li>Trust your gut. If something feels off, leave.</li>
    <li>If you feel unsafe or witness something wrong, use the report button. If there's an emergency, call 911 first.</li>
</ul>

<h2>How moderation works</h2>
<p>
    We review every report. Depending on what we find, we may remove the activity, warn the user, suspend the account,
    or permanently ban it. Severe violations (anything endangering minors, threats of violence, or coordinated abuse)
    skip warnings. We may also share information with law enforcement when legally required.
</p>

<h2>Appeals</h2>
<p>
    If you believe we made the wrong call, reply to the moderation email or contact us at the address below within
    14 days and we'll take a second look.
</p>

<h2>Contact</h2>
<p>
    Questions, feedback, or to flag something we should know about:
    <a href="mailto:trust@findactivity.local">trust@findactivity.local</a>
</p>

